## Data Sources for temp_metric

### 1. Temperature Data — ETL via `temperature_data_export_package`

ETL is handled by `temperature_data_export_package` (read-only, from `beehero-streamlit-app`).
Functions used: `load_sensor_samples()`, `load_gateway_samples()`, `add_hive_size_bucket()`.

Local samples are stored under `data/samples/group_{id}/{date}/` as Parquet files.

#### Sensor samples (`{id}_{date}_sensor_temperature.parquet`)

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `sensor_mac_address` | string | Hive sensor identifier |
| `timestamp` | datetime | 30-minute bin (resampled mean) |
| `pcb_temperature_one` | float | **Hive** internal temperature (°C) |
| `gateway_mac_address` | string | Gateway the sensor reported through |
| `group_id` | string | Hive group |
| `hive_size_bucket` | string | `'small'` / `'medium'` / `'large'` — derived from bee_frames |

#### Gateway samples (`{id}_{date}_gateway_temperature.parquet`)

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `gateway_mac_address` | string | Gateway device |
| `timestamp` | datetime | Measurement timestamp |
| `pcb_temperature_two` | float | **Ambient** (outdoor) temperature (°C) |

#### Hive updates (`{id}_{date}_hive_updates.parquet`)

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `sensor_mac_address` | string | Hive sensor |
| `created` | datetime | When the update was recorded |
| `group_id` | string | Hive group |
| `bee_frames` | int | bee frame count |
| `model` | string | Model version used for this date |

---

### 2. Hive Updates Query (Athena — raw DB)

Queried via `hive_updates_query()` from `src/model_monitor/ingestion/`.
The FROM table depends on the query date — always use the helper, never hardcode.

#### Table Source Switch — `supervised_beeframes` vs `unified_bee_frames` (IMPORTANT)

| Date range | Table |
|---|---|
| date ≤ 2026-03-09 | `data_lake_raw_data.supervised_beeframes` |
| date ≥ 2026-03-10 | `data_lake_raw_data.unified_bee_frames` |

**Rule:** always call `raw_bee_frames_table(date)` from `src/model_monitor/ingestion/` — never hardcode either table name.

---

### 3. Ground Truth (`data/temp_ground_truth/ground_truth_statuess_ca_2026.csv`)

Human-labelled model status per group per date. Source for `extraction_plan.py`.

| Column | Values | Description |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| `date` | `YYYY-MM-DD` | The evaluation date |
| `group_id` | int | Beekeeper group |
| `status` | `valid` / `invalid` / `needs_recalibration` | Human ground truth label |

**51 groups, 643 labelled dates** (as of 2026-03-26).

